commit.message:
encode unicode to utf8 before submitting to sha1

unicode.encode() uses the 'ascii' codec, and can't handle all unicodes: use 'utf8' to convert a unicode string to a byte array

commit.message: Increase toleranse to random fluctuations in tests

Merge pull request #6 from scivisum/feature/fix_shll_add_method

Fix python3 compatibility

Fix sliding hll update method, getting TypeError: unorderable types: int() > NoneType()
- also fixed some tests which were written for python2,  expecting integer division

We can't compare None with a number, so check that case, otherwise we get: TypeError: unorderable types: int() > NoneType()
- tests were failing because of this
